HEADWORD: Rou
<hw>Rou`⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
properly p. p. of <ets>rouer</ets> to break upon the wheel, fr.
<ets>roue</ets> a wheel, L. <ets>rota</ets>. See <er>Rotate</er>,
<er>Rotary</er>.]</ety> <def>One devoted to a life of sensual pleasure;
a debauchee; a rake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

